<font color="#666666" face="Verdana, Arial, Sans-serif" size="1">WACKY WEB WEEK<br><br></font>


<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="black" size="4"><b>

Purr-fection through yoga&nbsp;

</b><br></font>
<font face="Arial,Sans-Serif" color="black" size="1"><br></font>


<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="white" summary="Wacky Web Week">
<tr>
<td width="110" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/9073e3h/1i/?url=www.yogakitty.com%2F"> <img src="http://WindowsSecrets.com/images/wsn/W070419-yogakitty.jpg" align="left" width="110" height="100" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="3" title="Yoga Kitty" alt="Yoga Kitty"></a>
</td>

<td width="510" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">

<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" size="2">As if you need any more convincing that some 
people have <b>way</b> too much time on their hands, check out Yoga Kitty, a 
tongue-in-cheek Web site purportedly aimed at helping you and your pet cat enjoy 
the benefits of yoga, together. <br>
<br>
The centerpiece of the project is a handful of 
downloadable videos (in English and French) demonstrating a human-kitty </font>
<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="#000000" size="2">
team clearing past karmas, exploring meditation, and dispelling static cling. 
T-shirts and video tapes available.
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/9073e3h/?url=www.yogakitty.com%2F" name="ws_wacky web week">
More&nbsp;info</a><br></font>

</td>
